<div class="article-headline" id="Headline">WARM APPLE CIDER</div>



<div class="article-in-image" id="image1"><img src="images/page067.article001.image1.jpg" class="article-in-image" alt=""/></div>
<div id="separatorLine"> <div class="invisible">empty</div> </div>

<div class="articleImageCredit" id="ImageCredit">PHOTOGRAPHY BY SARAH SWIHART</div>
<div class="article-body" id="Body"><p class="no-indent">Makes 15 to 20 servings </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1 (6-inch) square cheesecloth </p><p class="no-indent">1 tablespoon whole cloves </p><p class="no-indent">4 cinnamon sticks </p><p class="no-indent">4 cardamom pods </p><p class="no-indent">2 (64-ounce) bottles apple cider </p><p class="no-indent">1 (32-ounce) bottle orange juice </p><br/><p class="no-indent">1. Place cloves, cinnamon sticks, and cardamom pods on cheese-cloth. Pull corners up, and tie with kitchen string. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">2. In a large Dutch oven, combine cider, orange juice, and spice bundle. Cook, stirring occasionally, over medium heat for 30 to 45 minutes. Remove and discard spice bundle before serving. </p><br/><p class="no-indent">Note: Spices not wrapped in cheesecloth may be added to cider mixture and heated as directed. Strain and discard them from cider mixture before serving.</p></div>
